caption: The quintessential neighborhood bar. Paddy Long’s always has a selection of amazing beers on tap, great food, and the friendliest staff. When I lived in the neighborhood I was sure to make it to Paddy’s at least once a week, and even after moving further south the place’s draw has kept me coming back. Can’t recommend enough.

Please dont crucify me for saying this but....it was damn near too much bacon. Lol...but my bf thought it was PERFECT! Definitely The Go-To spot for bacon lovers. Service was fantastic! The waiter explained the different types of bacon as soon as he brought them to the table. We would absolutely return.
Very much enjoy the food here.
Craft beer. Craft bacon. What else in life could you possibly need?!
great food, great staff!

Paddy's is a fantastic place to eat and drink in Chicago. Not a bad meal on the menu, the cleanest taps in town, and a knowledgeable staff. Doesn't get better...it just doesn't. And where else are you going to get a full Irish that good?  Do yourself a favor and make Paddy Long's your local!
Not much to eat because of St. Patrick's.
Great Guinness and bacon!
The food, beer selection, and especially the staff are all excellent. Try the bacon poutine!
Bacon board, fried pickles and a sour beer. Doesn’t get better!
Ok beer selection but was expecting more from the bacon offerings in both variety and flavor.

Love Paddy Long's! It's the best neighborhood bar in Lakeview. All of the staff are super nice, friendly, and welcoming. They always have an awesome selection of craft beers and it rotates so there is often something new to try! They also have unique cocktails and a good whiskey/bourbon selection. My hub and I like all of the food we've had here  (and there are good choices for non-bacon eaters, too)! The atmosphere is chill and they always have music and sports on. They choose to work with ethical companies and have events that give back to nonprofit organizations. I love this place so much!
Love the atmosphere, the staff and the food.
Food and atmosphere were great, the bar staff was friendly and engaging. Will be back again when I'm out in Chicago. The Welsh Rarebit was delicious!
Great food and very friendly and attentive staff
Always a good place for a beer and a snack
The bartender was awesome and had a nice beard
The best place in the city for a burger and some really good beers
What's not to like about great beer, interesting drinks and a 5 pound meatloaf sandwich wrapped in bacon for $80?
Wonderful food, incredible service, amazing beer and bacon
Phenomenal service, delicious and interesting food items (bacon gravy on the poutine is just pure awesomeness), and great drinks.
Reasons to visit: Bacon. Great atmosphere. Bacon. Uber friendly staff. Bacon. Great cocktails and beer selection. Also, bacon.  My only regret is that I didn't go in sooner.
Best beer and bacon pub in Chicago. If you want a cool bar with a Irish feel and a place to watch rugby come on over!
Good stand by place in a rapidly changing neighborhood

HUGE bacon fan, so why not come here? The bartender was only one working but of course it was late when we went. He was very friendly and inquisitive (where y'all from, how you know about us, etc). Had the bacon bomb sandwich, which was a little spicy but good. Tried to ask for no sauce but think it was already on bomb, so no biggie. All around nice place, ESPECIALLY if you're a bacon fan
Fantastic neighborhood place to eat great food and drink the best beer in the city.
Great Burgers and fries! Really good deals on the weekday. Nice staff.

The concept is great. However most of the bacon came out still undercooked and not crispy.  I really would live for them to fix it. They have so much potential.  And no dessert of any kind. What an opportunity missed.

This restaurant is surely one of the tastiest place in the region. Always when I come there I am absolutely glad. They keep their high  level service and the topmost level of cooking  they give. You no doubt will love this place. Highly  recommended.
Visited during a pop-up event with Czech food and drink specials. Had a great time trying new food and new beer.
Nice staff and great cod fish.
Food was excellent and staff was I took a party of 13 they all loved it. I highly recommend this place for you bacon lovers.
Server was very curt
Nice bar good burgers Bacon's great check it out you may like it.
Has the 3 B's of success. Bacon beer and bacon. Seriously, good food, good drinks, friendly staff
They ask the question is bacon an entre? The answer: it is. Great food, great beer deals. Check it out. 10/10 would eat again.
Great little place for a burger and a beer. Get the beer of the month or take your chances on a cheap beer roulette!

Best Bacon in the City! The board of bacon, the bacon cheeseburger, Wings, curry fries, and the bacon bomb were delicious!! They have good beer on tap and in stock also! If you are a bacon fanatic and in the Chicagoland area...You gotta go to Paddy Long’s!!
Definitely come for the bacon.  We were here with a beer tasting group, so we were on a limited menu and schedule.  The bacon was great tho.
So fun after a Cubs game...come here for all sorts of bacon delights (and other things). YUM and a great staff to help you through your first experience!
Good vibes
If you love bacon, this is the place to go! Basically bacon-themed everything. Also, the staff was super nice!
Great pub
(Translated by Google) Rich food and beers  (Original) Rica comida y Cervezas
Finally got to try it. Food was awesome!
Local bar with great atmosohere

Ordered the bomb, it is basically a giant bacon wrapped meat loaf but it actually tasted good and it comes with a giant basket of fries.  Decent selection of beer to choose from.  The service was great but had no a/c or it wasn't working or didn't have it on yet but overall a decent bar to go to

Love this spot. Great staff, comfortable and chill vibe, good beer (and other drinks), and good drunk food. Exactly what you want a neighborhood bar to be. They also stepped up their whiskey game recently which I appreciate.
Nice late night place. Good selection of beers.
(Translated by Google) Food good and choices of chopp, I found it a bit dark and old.  (Original) Comida boa e opções de chopp, achei um pouco escuro e antigo.
Painfully loud, but delicious.

Beer and bacon. Bacon and beer. So this place isn't heart healthy. But just like the west side's Kaiser Tiger, you'll gladly ditch whatever diet you're on to plow through their food, at least for one night.
Best place I been to in a long time I loved it!
Great place, great staff.
Great beer place
Great neighborhood bar.  Low key with great food.
Great food and service. Can't wait to come back and try some other plates.
Known for the bacon, but you can also go for the Reuben! Marinated, thick-cut corned beef was fantastic! Great service too.
Really good food with a nice and extensive beer menu
Great beer and cider choices. Bartender was friendly and knowledgeable.
Oh yes! It's all about the bacon...love the bacon grenades!! Always get the bacon board! They are the best!
Great bacon platter and beer selection.
The bacon poutine was great, made exactly how it should be!
It's great bacon filled food and delicious beer.  What else do you need???

Had a great experience here tasting the multiple types of bacon on the bacon board. In addition there were plenty of good brews to choose from making the experience even better. The staff was very friendly and the service was great, I'm looking forward to going back and bringing friends.
Fantastic beer line up, and the food is great.  If you like meat, or more specifically bacon, go here.  Bomb Sandwich, baby!  The bartenders are great.  Anna's the best!

Food was TERRIBLE!! Service was good but we will never go back. Watched this place on a show for Chicago's good food. But was NOT good. My husband and I both got the Bomb sandwich. I couldn't even eat it.. Gross... We also got the appetizer breaded bacon. You cant even taste the bacon. All breading. I'm just so disappointed.

Paddy Long’s has the iconic “Bacon Bomb”. But if you don’t have the appetite or friends to share with, get the Bomb sandwich. It’s AMAZING! The bacon sampler is an insanely delicious appetizer. The beer is always an adventure with staple and eclectic brews that will compliment the bacon to a tee.

Bacon and Beer! What more can you ask for! Located steps from the Diversey Brown Line this local watering hole is a great spot to stop in for a pint, two or three. The staff is very friendly and if you are not sure what you want they can help you find something on tap or in cans/bottles. While they do have vegetarian options this is a carnivore's haven. If you have a group of 6 or more would highly recommend the whole bomb which is 5lbs of bacon, pork sausage and ground beef. (Elastic Waist Band Recommended)
Appears like an unassuming place that blends with the neighborhood pretty well, but this spot has some of the best beer around. They have specialty stuff tapping regularly and great food.
I know it's a bacon bar, but I'm a wing fanatic. 2 times I've been here and 2 times I've left completely happy with my wing order. Service was excellent and food came quickly.
Great beer list with a frequently updated list of local craft beers and imports. The food is always delicious too, especially if you like bacon!
Excellent selection of craft beer on tap and in bottles/cans. Good food, especially bacon

Best burger I've had in a while - charbroiled, with peppered bacon.  So yummy, no sauce necessary.  Great beer list with many Belgians available. OK... here again January 2019. Had bacon sampler- words not adequate to capture the bacon deliciousness of this platter. Yes, I ate it all. Me. Also great beer selection on rotating draft.
Excellent place to have a late night drink in a laid back setting when the TV'S are off so you can converse.  Rob was great behind the bar too!

Experienced the bacon/beer pairing.  Wow, what an awesome time.  Paddy's really knows their bacon.  Smaller venue, but that makes it fun.  Albie, our host,  did a great job of explaining the relationship between the bacon and beer.  Five pairings, great beers and even better bacon.  Already planning for next year.
Went for the bourbon country event. Great atmosphere, amazing bacon and superb service. Makes you feel right at home.

Tons of bacon and good beer. How could you not like it. Staff are super friendly and helpful. The food is amazing and they have dinner interesting local beer you won't find many other places. Get there.

we came for a beer. Unfiltered Pilsner.  But we are also bacon lovers.  I don't need to say anything else, we loved that place.  Bacon boards and beer, bacon wrapped dates (6 for $12 is too little guys how about 12/$12) and bacon granades were fantastic.  And no TVs on all night long, perfect. Rob, great service man. Thank you.
The BEST hamburger I have EVER had in my life!! And the Guinness Beef Stew is a warm piece of heaven.  Get the beef stew as a side in place of fries.
Great place and unbelievable atmosphere for the rugby games
Went for the bacon bomb sandwich for lunch. Unfortunately it was super dry this time. First time we had it, it was juicy and phenomenal.
Very good service and amazing atmosphere.

We visited this place last year, and the meatloaf/bacon sandwich was amazing. It was perfectly done. That's why we put it on our list when we came back. However, this time, I think it must have been a left over from the day before, it was very dried it out and the flavor was not the same.  In addition, it took a while to come out even though we got there shortly after they opened and we were the only people sitting down, and there were only two people at the bar.
Went here on a Sunday.. pleasantly surprised to get the Bears gamr with sound. The place wasn't too lound. The brunch menu was great with a good bloody mary. Great place with good food.
I always go just for the bacon options on the menu. Beer-battered bacon is amazing! Highly recommend!
Bartender rocked. Food was really good. Hi from your green tea ladies!
Staff is awesome. Bacon items are amazing

Had a fun. Time at Paddy Long's. Visiting from out of town and had dinner, beer and listened to music for their Oktoberfest celebration. Staff was very nice and attentive but a bit slow. That aside, we weren't in a hurry so it was all good.

Paddy Long's has one of the best BLTs I've ever had in my entire life. Seriously. I've yet to find one as good as the one here. I'm not even sure there are other items on the menu at this point. Just get the BLT. Stop reading this and order it already.
Gotta get the bacon flight and the bomb

Pub food with great beers & bacon tasting. Street parking but I would recommend getting by a train or taking a bus. We always get bacon board. It's pretty good. What makes Paddy an awesome place is the Pilsner Urquell event. Once in a while they will have the Pilsner Urquell night where you get the beers & keep the mugs. The kegs  flew in from Prague!
Best bacon / Irish pub in Chicago
BEST BURGER IVE HAD IN A LONG TIME! DEFINITELY RECOMMENDING TO MY FRIENDS
Fantastic
Excellent food and friendly staff!
Great place. Great food beer and service. Been a fan of this place from when we were lived down the street to today.

Not a bad place for a beer and some grub.  The bacon assortment is great but all the bacon dishes I sampled were bland.  Aside from the bacon, every dish tasted like it needed a pinch of salt.  Staff were seemingly annoyed by our visit.  Beer list is great but what made everything just "eh" was the staff.
Good Bloody Mary's
Decent beer selection but so very disappointed in the bacon and that’s the only reason I went.
Bacon, bacon, bacon luv it. Food is good and bartenders attentive

We went around 5:30pm and not many people were in there which was perfect to me. Tried some of the bacon appetizers, the bacon board was phenomenal as well was the appetizer that had a little bit of everything. Food was outstanding! Drinks were perfect as well! Definitely recommend.

This place was awesome.  Very comfortable and casual.  Staff was very friendly.  We sat at the bar and gad good conversation about bacon and vintage t-shirts. If you've never been, you have to go. Order the grenades, game changers.
Former kumas buddy tends bar there, ok spot.
Good tasting food at the right price!
Good place for eats if you in to bacon's bacon bacon
Great service!
Local spot for all your bacon and beer needs. Delirium is always on tap which is a huge plus.
Bacon board was amazing! Great selection of beer + soccer? = Awesome afternoon!
Good experience
Good food and great service! Cheap and fun place to watch a game. Jen is the best!
I make sure i get the bomb sandwich every time I'm in Chicago.  It never disappoints! Great prices on all the food.  Wish this place was where i live!
Clearly a spot that has been around for a bit decent taplist that focuses more on traditional styles. If you like Bacon and Beer this place is a great option.
Best sausage, bacon, whiskey.
What a name....  I ate so much bacon I almost got sick.

Wow! The bacon was bomb! De-li-cious! Nice and even cozy place, laid back with interesting beer selection. Staff was very nice, making sure that we had full glasses. Really fair local pub. And did I mention the bacon....😉
Great service and amazing food! This place is second to none in Chicago!
Bacon central!  The best in town!

Awesome local bar with really good food and an amazing beer selection. I've been going here since I moved here. It has great service and an amazing, local bar atmosphere. It's one of my favorites for a reason.
Awesome food with a great beer selection.

Terrible service, badly balanced menu, outdated beer list, clueless server and sub-par food.  We ordered the bacon board, which was alright for the price. The blt wasn't anything special. The signature salad I ordered was undressed and had almost no bacon or vegetables aside from the lettuce and parsley on the plate.  I tried to give the server the benefit of the doubt as he was running bar and dining room, but his attitude and inability to even stroll by to check on our table is inexcusable (especially since it wasn't busy at all while we were there).
Always a great selection of beers and the food is delicious.
Its a bacon centric pub - What more do you need to know? Great beer selection, very good food, and chill vibe in a great hood.  Definitely check it out.

We saw Paddy Long's on a dining show and stopped in for fun the last time we were in the city and recently returned during our last visit to try more of the menu. The food is beyond fabulous, especially if you love bacon, and their stock of beer, wine and ciders is a mile long. The staff is fast and upbeat, very welcoming.
Beer and bacon bar, need I say more? Great selection of beer, solid menu, intimate without being too formal. Great spot all around.
Was a nice Pub experience. I went for the morning special for the 6 Nations rugby games.  Nice environment. Beware Bacon may come out SUPER fatty or burnt. Other then that I would recommend.
(Translated by Google) Pleasant place, cozy atmosphere.  (Original) Local aprazível, ambiente acolhedor.

Stumbled in while bar hopping in the neighborhood. The staff was great, super friendly, and helpful. We only got appetizers, but they were good. The beer list is FANTASTIC! They had Delirium on tap! A great selection of various types of beer on tap, and a vast and expansive bottle and can list. The staff was knowledgable and helped navigate the beer menu. I will definitely be back.

One of my favorite spots. Solid draft list with amazing specials. Frequently features limited run barrels from international brewers. Boasts a truly impressive whiskey selection in a part of town rife with good whiskey bars. The food is, obviously, very heavy on bacon, and British and Irish inspired, but this is bacon with dignity. Get the bacon board. You never knew there were so many ways of doing bacon.

Had a great late lunch here. Had the Bacon Bomb again with lots of leftovers which is a good thing!! The bartender/waiter was great too! Had a fun time with him. The beer selection here is amazing!! The hummus is quite delicious also.
The best food for a bar!!! The cook rocks!
Excellent beer and food selection whether or not you like bacon.

An awesome place with a great selection of beer and multiple kinds of bacon. They also feature a beer of the month offered on tap for a low price! Paddy Longs also hosts a lot of tap takeovers from local breweries, so it’s worth keeping up with what they are doing next. Great friendly staff and a wonderful place to stop if you’re in the neighborhood.
Delicious!
Great whiskey deals Thursdays.
Good food but I wouldn't try the food challenge. Doesn't taste good
Great quaint spot. Really tasty food and exceptional staff
Awesome

I can honestly say that my visits to Paddy Long’s are the best bacon experiences I’ve ever had.  They have a half dozen different types, all cured in-house, and all absolutely delicious.  Their beer selection and other menu items complement the bacon perfectly.  The staff is excellent and the pub is located just a half block west of a Brown Line stop.

A bar with a focus on bacon? What can't you love about it. I've been here for brunch, lunch, dinner, and late night - and every visit was great. They have a top notch beer selection plus an awesome jukebox. Did I mention the bacon focused menu?

Beer and bacon, yes please. If you havent tried it jowel bacon is the greatest thing ever made. They have a "bomb" sandwich which is simply amazing. Also you can ask for a mystery 3 dollar beer, my buddy got a great Irish ale, I got an ice house.... Still fun.
Great beer and bacon!
Bacon. Bomb.
Great beer list and bacon-based food

I went to Paddy Long's with a crew of 5 guys to get the Paddy Bomb. What is it? It's 6lbs of meat wrapped in bacon, served with buns and french fries. We went around 1pm on a Sunday and the place was nearly empty (maybe 2 other tables) which was fine since the waitress/bartender was really nice and attentive anyways. The bomb looked as formidable as it sounds, and while cooked thoroughly, it was a little cold. It was good, in the sense that it's meat and bacon, but at the same time tasted a bit bland without the BBQ sauce. It's definitely a fun thing to do with a crew, but eh wouldn't have to do it again.
A great neighborhood bar with nice drafts for beer enthusiasts and great food for bacon and pork lovers.
Bacon bacon bacon! Great brunch and beer and whiskey selections!
We are regulars at this brewery and love it.
Really good staff. Solid beer choices. The everything-is-bacon thing is gimmicky, but there's really nothing wrong with the food. I like this place.
Bacon board was tasty and so were the drafts we had. No option for a flight but they did have 5oz options.
Great beer selection. Enjoyed the outside patio. Service was okay. Food was yum.
Best bacon in the city!
Bacon grenades...
Love this place!!!!
OMG bacon! Need I say more? Fun spot with a local feel
I love their rooftop deck!!!
Great beer selection
The bar staff is very knowledgeable in the world of beer and make great recommendations.
Cozy and chill with a great beer selection and good food!
Good dive-ish bar.  Make sure to try a pint of bacon
Try the bacon and beer pairing--the House Danish Bacon with the Tighthead Hat Trick was my favorite.

I get seduced by the front patio into coming in here every time. Every time! And yet i forgot to take a picture of it! They have an excellent better selection, but it's kind of pricey. Good was good and interesting. Crowd was cool and so was the staff. Come here!
Great beer, great bacon!

First time here, the bartender was fantastic and very personable. The food was amazing. Bacon platter and fried pickles. Not to mention the great beer selection.  I went there on a Monday, and at that time they have half price appetizers

Worst service ever. The waitress was completely careless. We had to wait forever to be served. She took our order in a super rush, as a consequence our food came different from what we ordered. She was rude and insisted that 'this is how we do it!'. She did not change the burger, this is how you don't do it!
What more could you want in a bar.  Excellent beer selection and bacon. Lots of bacon.  Also home to my favorite spicy chili.
Eclectic menu, with a diverse variety of offerings, the food was wonderful.  Beer offerings Lzo were on point.  Like the safe Lincoln Park location, as well.
You saw the title - they have beer AND bacon - end of story.
Good beer! and as they say everything is better with bacon!    Go
Great, attentive bartenders
It's a Bacon & Beer Pub, go and enjoy!
Easily my favorite bar. Diverse mix of people and great beer selection. Food is great.

I've always been a fan of this place.  Amazing bacon variety and craft beer selections.  Did a beer and bacon pairing recently and it was well worth the cost for the reservation.  The peppered bacon was one of my favorites.
Good beer and amazing burger! Fun atmosphere to hang out, watch a game, and not that crowded so you can have a conversation with those around you.
The Bomb!!!  BBQ sauce is quality.  The service is great (Alvie rocks)
Mmm bacon
The fried bacon was fun and they have a Guinness-like beer on tap. A good little pub.

Horrible service. The waitress came to us once  and then didn't come back for over 20 minutes, talking to other tables and dropping stuff off at tables near us, then would just bolt back behind the bar before asking if we needed anything. Our drinks were nearly empty and we still hadn't ordered food which is what we came there to do. Finally I went to the bar and asked her politely if she could come over and take our order when she had a minute. She came to our table five minutes later with a horrible attitude and was extremely rude. Then still just dropped stuff off at the table after that and would run away without asking if we needed anything else. The food was not even that great. It was mediocre at best but and not live up to the bacon bar hype. Bad service, mediocre food. Atmosphere was nice, but overall would probably not recommend.

I Love Paddy Long's  grrat selection of beer and spirits  and the whole menu  consists  of bacon!! I Love the Bomb i come every year with my family  for my birthday. The  panini is great as well as the quesadilla and the bacon board.... A must go even if its once!
Love this place
Best bacon around
Amazing bacon platter andade us espresso martinis on the fly
Paddy panini was delicious
Amazing bacon. I didn't even know bacon like this existed
BACON AND BEER. What more could you want?
Pat has taken two of the greatest things man has ever made and paired them together to make a slice of heaven on earth
Bacon everything! Can't go wrong by stopping in. Can be tough to grab a table depending on time of day.
Not my type of place.
Bacon and beer is the greatest
BACON!!!! NEED I SAY MORE

OMG the 3 bacon burger I don't have the words for how good this was and that bacon is a work of art! My favorite burger in Chicago now! And a big selection of craft beers. The two I tried were delicious - a citrus beer and a chocolate beer. Wow!!
It's a bacon themed bar. Enough said.
Beat bacon in town
Good beer selection
Great helpful bar staff. Amazon bacon

Paddy's had amazing brews, local options and great food too! The staff is what makes the place. Your bartender knows tons about beer, mixed drinks and even the dreaded Malort! I love it enough to rarely tell people about it because I don't want it to change lol
Amazing food and staff. Trivia night on Tuesdays is a blast and $5 beers of the month help keep a few extra coins in my pocket!
Bacon, craft beer and sports on the TV.
Amazing food and so much delicious delicious bacon.  Great beer.  Helpful quick service
It pretty much says it all in the name. Good beer list, better meat.
Amazing bacon plus great local beers, how can you go wrong?
The burgers actually get better with every bite. By the time your at the end it's so saturated with bacon juice that your mouth with actually explode with a delightful orgasm of flavor and happiness.
Go for the beer and stay for the bacon (and beer). They have a great burger as well. With good food and good drinks, you won't be disappointed here.
Good spot for drinks and appetizers (especially the bacon).
Great beer! It's my favorite pub!
Pretty good food and decent beer selection for a reasonable price.

Perfect neighborhood spot! Great for a weeknight drink, day drinking on the weekend, and some solid apps (bacon is a recurring theme on their menu). Short of 5 stars only because my eggs benedict at brunch one day had nearly hard boiled eggs.
The Guinness stew was really good.
Great drinks and the best bacon tasting in the city.
Bacon apps were great and the Giganator BLT is really good. Excellent beer selection and try the bacon infused boubon. Best part is they have real people inside.
Amazing

We came in on a Sunday and had the best service from Kristin. She really took care of us. I made a mistake and thought the beer and Bacon pairing was on Sunday but it's on Saturday. She made sure we didn't leave without taking their awesome Bacon. If you want a quick stop through here take the walking Brewery/bar tour. They stopped in and brought the party with them! The bacon was amaze-balls!
Really chill neighborhood bar. Decent food and nice beer selection. Great place to hang any night of the week

Been waiting to go here for a while and was pretty disappointed. Me and a few buddies wanted to try the big bacon bomb for 70 bucks but thankfully did not and went with the bomb sandwich. It was basically a very dry reheated meat loaf. The beef stew was microwaved and absolutely horrible texture and taste wise. My buddies that got burgers were not impressed either.  We all got beer and the majority of us felt as if it was a bit watered down. Definitely would not recommend the place.
Get the bomb Sandwich. done. oh and a beer.
Amazing selection of brew, the bee cider is delicious and the chicken pesto panini is the best panini I've ever had
Great beer and bacon selection :)
Asked to try various beers and they brought samples. 5 out of 5.
The bomb: brown sugar and pepper and bacon! Taste amazingly awesome!

Love Paddy Long's!  The food is great and it is never too loud.  I was a little upset last that they forgot my order when they brought out the food to our table.  They totally made up for it though by not charging me for my sandwich.  I will definitely be back!
Local pub - a very nice local pub.  Great selection of draft beers and the beer-battered chicken finger are to die for (in all senses). Service is friendly and great.

They have a great vibe, great bartenders (see Sam) and a solid beer & food menu.  When it's packed it's standing room only, and you're most likely rubbing shoulders with the person behind you, which gets you to want to leave rather quickly.  Aside from when it is packed, I really dig this place.

Apparently I'm the only person in the world who isn't all that crazy about bacon, but that doesn't stop me from loving Paddy's. This is a great neighborhood bar that's completely unpretentious. If you're in the area, Paddy's should be your go-to bar for a drink with friends. Good food and great beer. What else do you need?
Great beer selection!
Bacon bomb? Yes. Yes please.

A big ole' meh. The woman I spoke with on the phone when I called about a missing credit card was incredibly rude and put me on hold before I could even spell the name on the card. The food was great, but the service was so bad that I'll never go back.

Great local bar for a drink during the week/happy hour. It's never crowded but there are always people there. It's on the quite side which is by design I think. late twenties early thirties crowd. Solid selection of whiskey. The owner is a very nice guy who takes time on each person he serves.

So, this place is a "bacon bar," and I shouldn't have to write much more. Came across them first at Baconfest, then went back with a Groupon to do the beer and bacon pairing. Delicious -- different preparations of the bacon with good beer choices. Solid experience. Thinking I need to go back sometime to try The Bomb with some friends.
I loved it! Saw on TV and experienced it in person. Next challenge it's the Bacon BOMB!

Awesome food and great beer selection. The bomb sandwich is amazing and the all the types of bacon are great. The peppered bacon is the best. Tons of beer on a rotating tap list that are generally all good.
The BBQ burger is awesome, better than the meatloaf bomber sandwich. Great service. Good street parking. Friendly staff.

Went here after seeing it on Chicago's Best episode.  Typical bar/pub atmosphere with decent food. Tried the Bacon Grenades, Bacon Bomb sandwich, and Bacon BBQ Burger. The Bacon Bomb was a bit dry and had a heavy amount of black pepper …
Loved it. Was great atmosphere and the people were wonderful!
cozy decor. very nice in the winter for a brew!

This shrine to bacon and beer is a wonderful little spot on the border between lakeview and lincoln park.  Come for the bacon and beer tastings or the various tap takeovers that the bar hosts.  Whatever brings you out, you're sure to have a great time at this popular yet laid back beer bar.

If you want to raise morale in your office, do as we did and get a BOMB TO GO!  Paddie's packs up the BACON BOMB with sauce, a double large portion of French fries and rolls.    The perfect Friday feast! Because of the take-out restrictions, had to stop at the package store in the next block east for Dos Equis and Corona --- probably not the optimum for the BOMB but heartily enjoyed by our office.  It fed six well and still had just under half left for those who had to toil on Saturday. Cost? about the same as lunch for two at the Rosebud's in our building!  It makes you feel so happy for the rest of the day! David Blocher,   Law Offices of David Blocher, the blue-collar lawyer

This is a fun place to go if you have an appetite for bacon. You should be open to the fact that some types are much fattier than others, but overall, the beer and bacon tasting is a great time. I recommend that you go with a group. The service is good and there is a lot to do in the area when you leave the bar.
Keep it simple. Jonah's top 3 points. -over priced (bacon isn't always cooked) -parking is difficult to find. Walk or ride a bike (welcome to the area). -friendly slow service

Amazing food, great beer election, friendly staff. Obviously a local favorite, as the place was packed out. The Guinness beef stew was wonderful, but not for everyone

Bacon, beer and rum. A great experience at a Mom and Pop feeling kind of joint. The bacon bombs were amazing and the Founders Breakfast Stout was a perfect match for it. Nothing complicated, just good food, good drinkies and good people. We mingled with several and everyone was friendly. 2 thumbs up!
Great beer, get there early before it gets too crowded.

Drove up from Indiana to try out Patty Long's after seeing it featured on " the United States of Bacon".  We took the kids with after calling first to make sure kids could go to the pub.  We went on a Monday and we able to get half off on appetizers.  The bacon tray was great, but the bacon grenades stole the show.  We also had the wings which were better than most wing places.  I tried the monster BLT which was a true flavor explosion.  I will be going back in a month or two to try out more items.  A very nice restaurant and bar.
My favorite bar in the city--not just because its a block away from home. Outstanding beer selection and pretty good food. Friendly people too!
Great place to grab a beer and hangout with friends. Friendly and knowledgable staff. GREAT BACON!!!!
